Redford also admonished Hoskins for dumping the body, robbing the family of a chance to have a proper funeral for their loved one.

Maze' mother, Wanda Rose, spoke before Hoskins was sentenced and recalled the difficult task of trying to explain to her grandchildren about their mother's death.

Hoskins said in his piece that he loved Maze and worked hard to support her and her daughter.

'Before this happened, everybody looked at me as a good person,' Hoskins said. 'In the blink of an eye, I'm a monster.'

